  <p class="lead">Blinkit (formerly Grofers, now owned by Zomato) is India&rsquo;s leading quick-commerce platform, delivering groceries and everyday essentials in minutes from a dense network of dark stores across 25+ cities. For brands, it is one of the highest-velocity sales channels available in India today.</p>
  <p>However, getting onboarded on Blinkit involves multiple stages &mdash; documentation, KYC, Category Manager approvals, commercial negotiation, catalog creation, multi-state GST compliance, inventory planning, and operational integration. Done right, the process is smooth and fast. Done wrong, brands stall for weeks at &ldquo;application under review.&rdquo; This is where IARDO comes in.</p>
  <p>IARDO provides <strong>end-to-end Blinkit onboarding services across PAN India</strong>. As an authorized Amazon Seller Acquisition Partner operating since 2016 under founder Manish Madan, we have onboarded 2500+ brands across marketplaces and quick-commerce platforms &mdash; and we bring that same expertise to your Blinkit launch.</p>
  <p>Whether you are searching for a reliable <strong>Blinkit onboarding agency</strong>, need help with <strong>Blinkit seller registration</strong>, or simply want to know how to become a Blinkit seller and start selling, this page has you covered &mdash; the full process, the documents required, costs, timelines, the cities we serve, and exactly how IARDO gets your brand live on Blinkit faster and without avoidable rejections.</p>

