  <h2 id="mistakes"><span class="hash">#</span>Common Blinkit Onboarding Mistakes to Avoid</h2>
  <p>Most onboarding delays are self-inflicted. These are the mistakes that most often stall a Blinkit application &mdash; and exactly what IARDO helps you avoid so you don&rsquo;t lose weeks to re-submissions:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Name mismatches</strong> across GST, PAN, and bank records &mdash; the single most common rejection reason.</li>
    <li><strong>Missing FSSAI</strong> for food and grocery SKUs, discovered only mid-process.</li>
    <li><strong>Incomplete or non-compliant catalogs</strong> &mdash; wrong image standards, missing attributes, or weak titles.</li>
    <li><strong>Pricing without the full cost of selling</strong> baked in, leading to thin or negative margins after launch.</li>
    <li><strong>Skipping multi-state GST</strong> for the states where Blinkit&rsquo;s dark stores will stock you.</li>
    <li><strong>Going silent with the Category Manager</strong>, which slows approvals and commercial sign-off.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>Avoiding these is often the difference between going live in weeks versus months.</p>

  <h2 id="glossary"><span class="hash">#</span>Blinkit Seller Terms Explained</h2>
  <p>New to quick commerce? Here are the key terms you&rsquo;ll come across during Blinkit onboarding:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Dark store</strong> &mdash; a delivery-only micro-warehouse from which Blinkit fulfils 10-minute orders; your inventory is distributed to these.</li>
    <li><strong>Category Manager</strong> &mdash; the Blinkit team member who approves your listing, agrees commercial terms, and signs the seller agreement.</li>
    <li><strong>SKU</strong> &mdash; Stock Keeping Unit; a single, distinct product variant you list and sell.</li>
    <li><strong>Purchase Order (PO)</strong> &mdash; Blinkit&rsquo;s order to you to supply stock, generated based on real sell-through.</li>
    <li><strong>Multi-state GST</strong> &mdash; adding each warehouse state to your GST as an Additional Place of Business, so Blinkit can stock you across regions.</li>
    <li><strong>Fill rate</strong> &mdash; the percentage of a purchase order you actually fulfil; keeping this high protects your listing&rsquo;s health and visibility.</li>
  </ul>

